# Navy Yard Games App

Static site showing Washington Nationals games, Nationals Park events, and Audi Field events with traffic impact indicators.

## Data Flow

1. Build scripts (`scripts/fetch_*.js`) fetch data from APIs
2. Data is saved as static JSON in `data/`
3. Frontend (`app.js`) reads only local JSON — no browser API calls

## Key Files

- `index.html` — single-page entry point
- `app.js` — frontend logic, reads `data/*.json`
- `styles.css` — styling via CSS custom properties
- `data/` — prebuilt JSON (`nats.json`, `audi.json`, `natspark.json`)
- `scripts/` — Node build scripts for fetching data
- `icons/` — SVG icons and PWA assets

## Time Zones

- Store times as UTC in JSON; display in Eastern Time (`America/New_York`)
- Handle DST transitions automatically

## Traffic Impact Colors

- Home games/events = red (high impact)
- Away games = yellow (moderate impact)
- No events = green (low impact)
- Use consistent color coding across all cards

## PWA

- Service worker disables caching for fresh data
- Manifest supports home screen installation
- Icons use "DC" branding

## Build & Deploy

- Run `npm run fetch` or `./scripts/fetch_all.sh` to update data
- No compilation — serve static files directly
- Deploy to any static host (GitHub Pages, Netlify, etc.)

## Data Sources

- MLB Stats API for Nationals games (team ID 120)
- Nationals Park events page for non-MLB events
- Audi Field iCal feed (`ical.js` for parsing)
- Handle API failures gracefully with fallback messaging
